{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, commercial Klarite substrates were used to examine the SERS signals from PS MPs.",
    "These substrates use Au so they were excited using 785-nm excitation.",
    "Klarite generated a lower EF at 785 nm than AgF@AgM@C10 at 532 nm.",
    "The EF values obtained for Klarite are lower compared to the results reported by Zhang et al.",
    "12 for smaller PS beads (0.36 to 5 µm), likely because the 30 µm PS particles cannot fit into the inverted pyramidal gratings of the Klarite sensor."
  ]
}